The Ijaw Youth Council (IYC) has hailed the appointment of Prof. Pondie Kemebradikumo, as the new managing director of Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC). Briefing newsmen in Yenegoa, the chairman Ijaw Youth Council Central Zone, Comr. Kennedy Olorogun described the appointment as a “round peg in a round hole.” He, however, urges Ijaws irrespective of political lines to support him in achieving his mandate. Olorogun also commended President Muhammadu Buhari for appointing an Ijaw son as acting MD of the board in line with the constitutional provisions of the board. He stressed that Ijaw people has long clamoured for this appointment which has finally been actualized by the grace of God. ‘’On behalf of the zone has heartily congratulated a father and leader, the newly appointed acting managing director of NDDC,’’ he said. Olorogun reassures Ijaw Youths in the zone will mobilize the needed support for their own, and also used this medium to appeal to the new MD not to let Ijaw Nation down. He urged Prof. Kemebradikumo to come up with developmental projects that will be of benefit the Ijaw Nation like supporting the zone in the ongoing Bayelsa Central and West road, and other big projects the NDDC can intervene. Olorogun also called on Ijaw leaders, political leaders, business titans and opinion leaders to support Prof. Kemebradikumo as the MD of the board just like the way Akwa-Ibom and other states supported their own when manning that same office.